# TFD Tracker — root rules (Cursor also loads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`)

1. At the start of substantive work, read **HANDOFF.md**, then **docs/PROJECT_MAP.md**, then **docs/AI_HANDOFF.md** (continuity + deploy/git notes).
2. Before ending a session or after a major feature: **update HANDOFF.md** (and session log); update **PROJECT_MAP**, **DEPLOY_UBUNTU.md**, or **public/data/README.md** when relevant; **commit + push** unless the user opts out. See **docs/AI_HANDOFF.md** for the full checklist.
3. **CURSOR_MEMORY.md** points at the same handoff docs.
4. Stack and API conventions: **`.cursor/rules/tfd-stack.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/tfd-api-state.mdc`**, **`.cursor/rules/memory-handoff.mdc`**.
